HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 175
BY REPRESENTATIVE LARVADAIN
TOPS: Requests that the Board of Regents, in consultation with Louisiana Works, study
potential changes to the Taylor Opportunity Program for Students (TOPS) with
respect to the TOPS-Tech award
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Board of Regents, in consultation with Louisiana Works, to study
3 potential changes to the Taylor Opportunity Program for Students (TOPS) with
4 respect to the TOPS-Tech award and to submit a written report of findings and
5 conclusions, including any recommendations for related legislation, to the House
6 Committee on Education not later than March 1, 2027.
7 WHEREAS, the state of Louisiana has made significant investments in workforce
8 development programs intended to increase access to postsecondary training and
9 industry-based credentials for students seeking employment in high-demand fields; and
10 WHEREAS, through the Taylor Opportunity Program for Students (TOPS), TOPS-
11 Tech awards offer postsecondary education opportunities for students to prepare for entering
12 Louisiana's workforce; and
13 WHEREAS, there has been discussion of the need for evaluating various aspects of
14 the TOPS-Tech award in terms of eligible programs, coverage of fees in addition to tuition,
15 and student eligibility requirements.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
17 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the Board of Regents, in consultation
18 with Louisiana Works, to study potential changes to TOPS with respect to the TOPS-Tech
19 award and to submit a written report of findings and conclusions, including any
